<br>
Warning this MIGHT be considered an exploit so might want to get verification before trying it.<br>
<br>
The way EQ checks for spell interupts is your char's position.  It checks when you start casting the spell, and when the spell goes off, and if there is a difference in position of your char, the spell is interupted.<br>
<br>
Now if you think about that, as long as you are in the same position when your spell goes off you can land the spell.  <br>
<br>
An example.  Thurg arena, small room 4 corners.  Dueled a warrior with no pet up.  Stood with my back in the corner as far as I could go, cast nuke, run around entire arena so warrior couldn't hit me, and then just ran back to the same corner right before spell went off.  Know what ? The nuke landed, and it worked 99% of the time.  It is an AWESOME technique for PVP.<br>
<br>
Another example, I use to farm Twilight Sea for cash.  I'd run around entire island and aggro every elemental.  Now if I stopped and tried to AE I'd get wasted from interupts with 50 mobs beating and pushing me.  So the trick was run to the castle side wall outside, and stand in the corner of the little alcove.  Wait for the elementals to come, put your back in the corner, and AE.  AE went off 90% of time that way where as without it I could never get one off.<br>
<br>
I know this still works because just last night I was on my horse when nuking, and moved forward 5 horse steps to cancel, then ended up moving back 5 steps. (didnt really realize at the time) and know what ? nuke still went off.  So I assume this is still working in game.  Easiest test is to go into a building, cast a nuke with back in a corner, and run around then go back to corner like I mentioned earlier for arena fight.  That be quickest way to tell if it still works.  I&quot;ll prob check tonight and post results.<br>
<br>
One more thing to help when not near a corner and you get hit during gating etc.  What I usually do is if mob hits me while gating you can tell if you are pushed back, I just try to guess how much and move forward the same amount I was pushed back.  Works well a lot of the times, and saves my life a lot, but hard to judge, its more luck, so doesnt work everytime.  But still something to try if you know for a fact you got pushed by a mob and will interupt anyway. <p>Lianad Staffborn<br>
62 Arch Mage<br>
Bertoxx</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lianadmagi>Lianad Magi</A> at: 1/22/03 11:30:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kshipper>kshipper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:41:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=515.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Channeling - why does it never work for me?</span><hr size=1> There has always been a problem where the server thinks you are still moving when you casting. To test this:  target yourself run foward and stop and cast a level one bolt spell. Try that over and over and make note that you can not do it 100 percent. Occasionaly you will see the message that you continue casting in spite of the movement (a good indicator that your channelling is working)<br>
<br>
The best way to insure your cast goes off 100 percent is to stop running and turn right or left slighty THEN cast. Other then getting hit or stunned by a mob I guarantee you your spells will go off. to test: do the same thing as above only add the turn before the cast. Watch how that spells goes off everytime now! /cheers <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274568 Kshipper Arch Mage</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyalria>Nyalria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 8:46:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=515.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Channeling - why does it never work for me?</span><hr size=1> Dex doesn't do @#%$ for channeling, according to GZ, and according to the tests i've seen, and according to the idea that who gives a rip, i'm not going out of my way to get dex.  A warrior, monk, or rogue with 305 dex.  Ask one how many times he's ever regained concentration while trying to cast a click spell...<br>
<br>
If you end a spell in a different loc then you started, a roll is made, based on your channeling skill.  If it's successful, you regain concentration.  Now whether the AA skill adds another role, or just increases the chances of the first one going off, i'm not sure.  Good way to get a channel off, as stated above:  Start it in a corner, run around like a monkey for a few seconds if you want, then at the very end, jam yourself back in the corner.  You wont even &quot;regain your concentration,&quot; the spell will just go off most the time.<br>
<br>
And I also agree muchly with the turning after stopping thing, helps a lot too in just general kiting/stopping to cast/etc.  has to do with the way the server and client update each other.  Funny cause I started doing that at level 1, cause I liked the swirling spell effects all around me, but wasn't till my friends wondered how i could always keep casting right after stopping even my lagging computer, that figured it was that. =P <p>Mistress Nyalria<br>
